ProMED-mail
<promed@promedmail.org>
[It remains unclear how any of the 4 Indonesian avian influenza virus cases
contracted infection. It should be noted that the numbers of cases and
fatalities in East Asia quoted at the end of this article agree with the
WHO cumulative totals of laboratory confirmed cases, except for the figures
relating to Indonesia. WHO still acknowledges only a single case and a
single death from avian influenza virus infection in Indonesia, and neither
the Indonesian authorities nor WHO cite the previously reported single
confirmed asymptomatic case of avian influenza virus infection. - Mod.CP]
